horizontally swooping upon them. And though the other boats, unharmed, still 
hovered hard by; still they dared not pull into the eddy to strike, lest that 
should be the signal for the instant destruction of the jeopardized castaways, 
Ahab and all; nor in that case could they themselves hope to escape. With 
straining eyes, then, they remained on the outer edge of the direful zone, 
